{
  "text": "Different neuronal [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] or cardiac pathologies are related to abnormalities in the function of different ion channels and/or regulatory subunits, such as K V 4.3 and the regulatory subunit DREAM. Thus, KChIPs starts to emerge as a realistic drug target, and IQM-266 could be considered as a new chemical tool that might allow a better understanding of: (i) DREAM physiological role; and (ii) the modulation of I A in pathological conditions. ",
